column168: ON 7/26/87 AT APPROXIMATELY 6:30 PM. A SOUTHERN RAIL DRIVER FOUND TRAILER C RZ 235233 ON THEIR YARD AND FLAMES WERESHOOTING OUT OF THE TRAILER.  THE D AYTIME TEMPERATURE AT THE RAIL WAS IN THE UPPER NINETY'S AND THE TEMPERATUR E AT THE TIME OF THE FIRE WAS 86 DEGREES.  BASED ON THIS THE TRAILER WAS 11 0-120 DEGREES INSIDE.  ALUCHEM INC HAD SKIPPED 42,500 LBS OF HYDRATED ALUMI NA (NON-HAZARDOUS) + 1 SKID 440#'S THAT THEY LISTED AS OXIDER (IT WAS LATER DISCOVERED THAT THE SKID WAS IN FACT  ORGANIC PEROXIDE). THE LABEL ATTACHE D TO THE BURNED CONTAINERS SHOWS THAT EXPOSURE TO TEMPERATRUES ABOVE 109 DE GREE F MAY CAUSE DECOMPOSITION + FLAMMABLE VAPORS.  SEVERAL EXPORTS INVESTI GATED THIS ACCIDENT AND DETERMINED THAT THE EXTREME HEAT HAD CAUSED THIS CH EMICAL TO IGNITE AND EXPLODE.  THEY SUGGESTED THIS TYPE OF PRODUCT SHOULD B E SHIPPED IN REFRIGERATED TRAILERS WHEN IT'S BEING SHIPPED INTO HOT, TROPIC AL TEMPERATURES.
